# Processing Records

::: columns
:::: {.column width=50%}
- **Record**: set of data that describes one item
  - record, database row,  structure, object, item, user-defined type (UDT), 
    compound data type
- **Field**: single piece of data within a record
- Write record to sequential access file by writing the fields one after
  the other
- Read record from sequential access file by reading each field until record
  is complete
::::
:::: {.column width=50%}
## Records

The data that is stored in a file is frequently organized in records. A record
is a complete set of data about an item, and a field is an individual piece
of data within a record.

\vspace{0.2in}

A [Record](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Record_(computer_science))
\parencite{wikipedia-record-2026} is a basic computer science concept.
Called user-defined type (UDT), compound data type, etc.  Anytime you
collect multiple fields together to form a compound set of data, you
have a user-defined type in a data processing system.
::::
:::

# Records

- A record is made up of multiple fields (name, id number, department)

